Reviewed the **Tobey-Maguire** draft (`src/blog/people/drafts/Tobey-Maguire.md`) with fresh eyes and appended a `FRESH EYES REVIEW` comment block at the bottom. No body edits.

**The two biggest issues I flagged:**

1. **No marriage or kids.** The whole piece rests on "he built a home out of people instead of a place" — yet it never mentions Jennifer Meyer (married 2007, divorce finalized 2020) or their two children. That's not just a biographical hole; it's the thesis under maximum pressure. What does a man who engineers uncertainty out of everything do when the one alliance he *can't* fully control dissolves? Currently absent.

2. **The Great Gatsby is the glaring miss in the DiCaprio section.** Tobey and Leo — the two teenage best friends — actually starred opposite each other, with Maguire as Nick Carraway, the watchful outsider narrating someone else's spectacle. Almost too on-the-nose for a 6w5, and a real payoff of the thirty-year friendship the section is trying to prove. (I also flagged *Pawn Sacrifice* and the poker/Ponzi clawback lawsuit as on-theme expansions, and noted the two-temperatures thesis is restated ~4x.)

I also called out what's working so the next pass preserves it — chiefly the empathy turn reframing the seal/bark cruelty through the food-stamps childhood, and the "concede the point" critic anchor.
